tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE InventoryData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  partner_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  supplier_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  inventory_item VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  quantity INT NOT NULL,
  last_updated TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
)
CREATE TABLE partners (partner_id INT PRIMARY KEY, partner_name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50), phone_number VARCHAR(15), location VARCHAR(100));
CREATE TABLE inventory (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(100), quantity INT, last_updated TIMESTAMP, partner_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (partner_id) REFERENCES partners(partner_id));

CREATE TABLE suppliers (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	supplier_name VARCHAR(255),
	location VARCHAR(255),
	email VARCHAR(255),
	phone_number VARCHAR(20)
);
CREATE TABLE partners ( partner_id INT PRIMARY KEY, partner_name VARCHAR(255), partner_email VARCHAR(255), partner_phone VARCHAR(15) );
CREATE TABLE suppliers ( supplier_id INT PRIMARY KEY, supplier_name VARCHAR(255), supplier_email VARCHAR(255), supplier_phone VARCHAR(15), supplier_address VARCHAR(255) );
CREATE TABLE inventory ( product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name VARCHAR(255), quantity INT, supplier_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (supplier_id) REFERENCES suppliers(supplier_id) );
CREATE TABLE inventory_logs ( log_id INT PRIMARY KEY, event_time TIMESTAMP, product_id INT, quantity_change INT, log_type VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES inventory(product_id) );
CREATE TABLE partners (partner_id INTEGER NOT NULL, partner_name TEXT NOT NULL, partner_type TEXT NOT NULL, contact_email TEXT NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (partner_id));
CREATE TABLE suppliers (supplier_id INTEGER NOT NULL, supplier_name TEXT NOT NULL, supplier_type TEXT NOT NULL, contact_email TEXT NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (supplier_id));
CREATE TABLE inventory (product_id INTEGER NOT NULL, product_name TEXT NOT NULL, quantity INTEGER NOT NULL, last_updated TIMESTAMP NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (product_id));

CREATE TABLE inventory_logs (log_id INTEGER NOT NULL, product_id INTEGER NOT NULL, log_description TEXT NOT NULL, log_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL, FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES inventory(product_id), PRIMARY KEY (log_id));
CREATE TABLE access_logs (log_id INTEGER NOT NULL, user_id INTEGER NOT NULL, log_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL, log_activity TEXT NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (log_id));
